  "text": "This section addresses the problem of finding out suitable descriptors to establish a similarity metric between segments and proposes a cost function based on the border detection theory. To segment SAR images under this approach, the mean gray level of the segments may not satisfactorily be applied on the region merging, due to the speckle influence mainly in small samples. In edge detection applications, it is commonly used the ratio of averages to infer about the presence of edges, instead of the difference of means, to provide a constant false alarm (cfar ) detector [CITATION_1] .",
